<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-106-504  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 106 504.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  March 6 1989 n304 p104(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Network provides public access to government database. (PublicElectronic Network)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A Public Electronic Network (PEN) has been launched in SantaMonica, CA to enable citizens to use their microcomputers to tapgovernment data bases and to send messages to city officials.andP;  Thenetwork runs on a Hewlett-Packard Co 9000 minicomputer.andP;  HPdonated $300,000 worth of hardware and Metasystems Design GroupInc donated $50,000 worth of Caucus software, a computerconferencing application.andP;  Citizen registration is free.andP;  Twentyterminals will be installed by the city in libraries, seniorrecreation centers and city hall.andP;  Santa Monica will also set upan electronic educational center which will allow schools to tapinto the city government's data base for use in classrooms.andP;  Thenew technology has been hailed as 'electronic democracy.'andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     NetworksPublic Electronic Network (Information retrieval system)National GovernmentPublic AdministrationInformation Storage and Retrieval.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>